#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1000
#, 
msgid "Package Management"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1001
#, 
msgid "Package Management is an often requested addition to the LFS Book."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1002
#, 
msgid "A Package Manager allows tracking the installation of files making it easy to remove and upgrade packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1003
#, 
msgid "And before you begin to wonder, NO&mdash;this section does not talk about any particular package manager, nor does it recommend one."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1004
#, 
msgid "What it provides is a roundup of the more popular techniques and how they work."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1005
#, 
msgid "The perfect package manager for you may be among these techniques or may be a combination of two or more of these techniques."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1006
#, 
msgid "This section briefly mentions issues that may arise when upgrading packages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1007
#, 
msgid "Some reasons why no package manager is mentioned in LFS or BLFS:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1008
#, 
msgid "Dealing with package management takes the focus away from the goals of these books&mdash;teaching how a Linux system is built."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1009
#, 
msgid "There are multiple solutions for package management, each having its strengths and drawbacks."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1010
#, 
msgid "Including one that satisfies all audiences is difficult."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1011
#, 
msgid "There are some hints written on the topic of package management."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:100-1012
#, 
msgid "Visit the _L3911_ and see if one of them fits your need."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1000
#, 
msgid "Upgrade Issues"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1001
#, 
msgid "A Package Manager makes it easy to upgrade to newer versions when they are released."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1002
#, 
msgid "Generally the instructions in the LFS and BLFS Book can be used to upgrade to the newer versions."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1003
#, 
msgid "Here are some points that you should be aware of when upgrading packages, especially on a running system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1004
#, fuzzy
msgid "If one of the toolchain packages (_A67_ , _A267_ or _A295_ ) needs to be upgraded to a newer minor version, it is safer to rebuild LFS."
msgstr "If one of the toolchain packages (_A67_ , _A267_ or _A295_ ) needs to be upgraded to a newer minor version, it is safer to rebuild LFS."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1005
#, 
msgid "Though you"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1006
#, 
msgid "may"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1007
#, 
msgid "be able to get by rebuilding all the packages in their dependency order, we do not recommend it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1008
#, 
msgid "For example, if glibc-2.2.x needs to be updated to glibc-2.3.x, it is safer to rebuild."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1009
#, 
msgid "For micro version updates, a simple reinstallation usually works, but is not guaranteed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1010
#, 
msgid "For example, upgrading from glibc-2.3.4 to glibc-2.3.5 will not usually cause any problems."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1011
#, 
msgid "If a package containing a shared library is updated, and if the name of the library changes, then all the packages dynamically linked to the library need to be recompiled to link against the newer library."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1012
#, fuzzy
msgid " (Note that there is no correlation between the package version and the name of the library. ) For example, consider a package foo-1.2.3 that installs a shared library with name _F880_ ."
msgstr " (Note that there is no correlation between the package version and the name of the library. ) For example, consider a package foo-1.2.3 that installs a shared library with name _F880_ ."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1013
#, 
msgid "Say you upgrade the package to a newer version foo-1.2.4 that installs a shared library with name _F881_ ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1014
#, 
msgid "In this case, all packages that are dynamically linked to _F880_ need to be recompiled to link against _F881_ ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1015
#, 
msgid "Note that you should not remove the previous libraries until the dependent packages are recompiled."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1016
#, 
msgid "If you are upgrading a running system, be on the lookout for packages that use _C2095_ instead of _C907_ to install files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:110-1017
#, 
msgid "The latter command is usually safer if the executable or library is already loaded in memory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:120-1000
#, 
msgid "Package Management Techniques"
msgstr "Techniques de gestion de paquets"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:120-1001
#, 
msgid "The following are some common package management techniques."
msgstr "Ce qui suit est une liste de techniques habituelles de gestion de paquets."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:120-1002
#, 
msgid "Before making a decision on a package manager, do some research on the various techniques, particularly the drawbacks of the particular scheme."
msgstr "Avant de prendre une décision sur un gestionnaire de paquets, faites une recherche sur les différentes techniques et notamment leurs faiblesses."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:121-1000
#, 
msgid "It is All in My Head!"
msgstr "Tout est dans ma tête!"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:121-1001
#, 
msgid "Yes, this is a package management technique."
msgstr "Oui, c'est une technique de gestion de paquets."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:121-1002
#, 
msgid "Some folks do not find the need for a package manager because they know the packages intimately and know what files are installed by each package."
msgstr "Certains n'éprouvent pas le besoin d'un gestionnaire de paquets parce qu'ils connaissent très bien les paquets et connaissent les fichiers installés par chaque paquet."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:121-1003
#, 
msgid "Some users also do not need any package management because they plan on rebuilding the entire system when a package is changed."
msgstr "Certains utilisateurs n'en ont pas besoin parce qu'ils planifient la reconstruction entière de LFS lorsqu'un paquet est modifié."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1000
#, 
msgid "Install in Separate Directories"
msgstr "Installer dans des répertoires séparés"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1001
#, 
msgid "This is a simplistic package management that does not need any extra package to manage the installations."
msgstr "C'est une gestion des paquets tellement simple qu'elle ne nécessite aucun paquet supplémentaire pour gérer les installations."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1002
#, 
msgid "Each package is installed in a separate directory."
msgstr "Chaque paquet est installé dans un répertoire séparé."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1003
#, 
msgid "For example, package foo-1.1 is installed in _F882_ and a symlink is made from _F883_ to _F882_ ."
msgstr "Par exemple, le paquet foo-1.1 est installé dans _F883_ et un lien symbolique est créé de _F882_ vers _F882_."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1004
#, 
msgid "When installing a new version foo-1.2, it is installed in _F884_ and the previous symlink is replaced by a symlink to the new version."
msgstr "Lors de l'installation de la nouvelle version foo-1.2, elle est installée dans _F884_ et l'ancien lien symbolique est remplacé par un lien symbolique vers la nouvelle version."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1005
#, 
msgid "The environment variables such as those mentioned in"
msgstr "Les variables d'environnement telles que celles indiquées à la"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1007
#, 
msgid "need to be expanded to include _F883_ ."
msgstr "ont besoin d'être étendues pour inclure _F883_."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:122-1008
#, 
msgid "For more than a few packages, this scheme becomes unmanageable."
msgstr "Pour plus que quelques paquets, ce schéma devient ingérable."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1000
#, 
msgid "Symlink Style Package Management"
msgstr "Gestion de paquet par lien symbolique"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1001
#, 
msgid "This is a variation of the previous package management technique."
msgstr "C'est une variante de la technique précédente."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1002
#, 
msgid "Each package is installed similar to the previous scheme."
msgstr "Chaque paquet est installé de façon similaire au schéma précédent."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1003
#, 
msgid "But instead of making the symlink, each file is symlinked into the _F190_ hierarchy."
msgstr "Mais au lieu de réaliser le lien symbolique, chaque fichier dispose d'un lien symbolique vers son équivalent dans la hiérarchie _F190_."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1004
#, 
msgid "This removes the need to expand the environment variables."
msgstr "Ceci supprime le besoin d'étendre les variables d'environnement."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1005
#, 
msgid "Though the symlinks can be created by the user to automate the creation, many package managers have been written using this approach."
msgstr "Bien que les liens symboliques peuvent être créés par l'utilisateur, pour automatiser la création, certains gestionnaires de paquets ont été écrit avec cette approche."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1006
#, 
msgid "A few of the popular ones are Stow, Epkg, Graft, and Depot."
msgstr "Parmi les plus populaires se trouvent Stow, Epkg, Graft et Depot."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1007
#, 
msgid "The installation needs to be faked, so that the package thinks that it is installed in _F291_ though in reality it is installed in the _F885_ hierarchy."
msgstr "L'installation doit être faussée, de façon à ce que chaque paquet pense qu'il est installé dans _F291_ alors qu'en réalité il est installé dans la hiérarchie _F885_."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1008
#, 
msgid "Installing in this manner is not usually a trivial task."
msgstr "Installer de cette manière n'est généralement pas une tâche triviale."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1009
#, 
msgid "For example, consider that you are installing a package libfoo-1.1."
msgstr "Par exemple, considérez que vous installez un paquet libfoo-1.1."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1010
#, 
msgid "The following instructions may not install the package properly:"
msgstr "Les instructions suivantes pourraient ne pas installer correctement le paquet :"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1011
#, 
msgid "The installation will work, but the dependent packages may not link to libfoo as you would expect."
msgstr "L'installation fonctionnera mais les paquets dépendants pourraient ne pas lier libfoo comme vous vous y attendriez."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1012
#, 
msgid "If you compile a package that links against libfoo, you may notice that it is linked to _F886_ instead of _F887_ as you would expect."
msgstr "Si vous compilez un paquet qui se lie à _F886_ au lieu de _F887_ comme vous le prévoyez."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1013
#, 
msgid "The correct approach is to use _E44_ strategy to fake installation of the package."
msgstr "La bonne approche est d'utiliser la stratégie _E44_ pour fausser l'installation du paquet."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1014
#, 
msgid "This approach works as follows:"
msgstr "Cette approche fonctionne ainsi :"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1015
#, 
msgid "Most of the packages do support this approach, but there are some which do not."
msgstr "La plupart des paquets supportent cette approche mais elle pose problème à certains."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:123-1016
#, 
msgid "For the non-compliant packages, you may either need to manually install the package, or you may find that it is easier to install some problematic packages into _F685_ ."
msgstr "Pour les paquets non compatibles, vous pouvez soit les installer manuellement soit trouver plus simple d'installer les paquets problématiques dans _F685_."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1000
#, 
msgid "Timestamp Based"
msgstr "Basé sur le temps"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1001
#, 
msgid "In this technique, a file is timestamped before the installation of the package."
msgstr "Avec cette technique, un fichier est balisé avec l'heure avant l'installation du paquet."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1002
#, 
msgid "After the installation, a simple use of the _C2096_ command with the appropriate options can generate a log of all the files installed after the timestamp file was created."
msgstr "Après l'installation, une simple utilisation de la commande _C2096_ avec les options appropriées peut générer une trace de tous les fichiers installés après que le fichier temps ne soit créé."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1003
#, 
msgid "A package manager written with this approach is install-log."
msgstr "install-log est un gestionnaire de paquets écrit avec cette approche."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1004
#, 
msgid "Though this scheme has the advantage of being simple, it has two drawbacks."
msgstr "Bien que ce schéma a l'avantage d'être simple, il a deux inconvénients."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1005
#, 
msgid "If during installation, the files are installed with any timestamp other than the current time, those files will not be tracked by the package manager."
msgstr "Si à l'installation, les fichiers sont installés sans balise de temps autre que l'heure actuelle, ces fichiers ne seront pas suivis par le gestionnaire de paquets."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1006
#, 
msgid "Also, this scheme can only be used when one package is installed at a time."
msgstr "De plus, ce schéma peut seulement être utilisé lorsqu'un seul paquet est installé à la fois."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:124-1007
#, 
msgid "The logs are not reliable if two packages are being installed on two different consoles."
msgstr "Les traces ne sont pas fiables si deux paquets sont installés dans deux consoles différentes."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:125-1000
#, 
msgid "LD_PRELOAD Based"
msgstr "Basé sur LD_PRELOAD"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:125-1001
#, 
msgid "In this approach, a library is preloaded before installation."
msgstr "Avec cette approche, une bibliothèque est préchargée avant l'installation."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:125-1002
#, 
msgid "During installation, this library tracks the packages that are being installed by attaching itself to various executables such as _C2095_ , _C907_ , _C2097_ and tracking the system calls that modify the filesystem."
msgstr "Pendant l'installation, cette bibliothèque poursuit les paquets qui sont installés en s'attachant à divers exécutables tels que _C2095_ , _C907_ , _C2097_ et la poursuite des appels système qui modifient le système de fichiers."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:125-1003
#, 
msgid "For this approach to work, all the executables need to be dynamically linked without the suid or sgid bit."
msgstr "Pour que cette approche fonctionne, tous les exécutables doivent être liés de façon dynamique sans le bit suid ou sgid."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:125-1004
#, 
msgid "Preloading the library may cause some unwanted side-effects during installation."
msgstr "Le préchargement de la bibliothèque peut provoquer des effets indésirables pendant l'installation."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:125-1005
#, 
msgid "Therefore, do perform some tests to ensure that the package manager does not break anything and logs all the appropriate files."
msgstr "Effectuez donc des tests pour vous assurer que le gestionnaire de paquets ne casse rien et journalisés tous les fichiers adéquats."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:126-1000
#, 
msgid "Creating Package Archives"
msgstr "Créer des archives de paquets"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:126-1001
#, 
msgid "In this scheme, the package installation is faked into a separate tree as described in the Symlink style package management."
msgstr "Dans ce schéma, l'installation d'un paquet est faussée dans un répertoire séparé comme décrit plus haut."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:126-1002
#, 
msgid "After the installation, a package archive is created using the installed files."
msgstr "Après l'installation, une archive du paquet est créée en utilisant les fichiers installés."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:126-1003
#, 
msgid "This archive is then used to install the package either on the local machine or can even be used to install the package on other machines."
msgstr "L'archive est ensuite utilisée pour installer le paquet soit sur la machine locale soit même sur d'autres machines."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:126-1004
#, 
msgid "This approach is used by most of the package managers found in the commercial distributions."
msgstr "Cette approche est utilisée par la plupart des gestionnaires de paquets trouvés dans les distributions commerciales."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:126-1005
#, 
msgid "Examples of package managers that follow this approach are RPM, pkg-utils, Debian's apt, and Gentoo's Portage system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:127-1000
#, 
msgid "User Based Management"
msgstr "Gestion basée sur les utilisateurs"

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:127-1001
#, 
msgid "This scheme, unique to LFS, was devised by Matthias Benkmann, and is available from the _L3912_."
msgstr "Ce schéma, unique à LFS, a été décrit par Matthias Benkmann et est disponible sur le _L3912_."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:127-1002
#, 
msgid "In this scheme, each package is installed as a separate user into the standard locations."
msgstr "Dans ce schéma, chaque paquet est installé en tant qu'utilisateur séparé dans les emplacements standards."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:127-1003
#, 
msgid "Files belonging to a package are easily identified by checking the user ID."
msgstr "Les fichiers appartenant à un paquet sont facilement identifiés grâce à l'identifiant de l'utilisateur."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:127-1004
#, 
msgid "The features and shortcomings of this approach are too complex to describe in this section."
msgstr "Les fonctionnalités et avantages de cette approche sont trop complexes pour les décrire dans cette section."

#. type: Content of: 
#: ./test3/introduction/important/pkgmgt.xml.1.chaine:127-1005
#, 
msgid "For the details please see the hint at _L3913_ ."
msgstr "Pour plus de détails, voir l'astuce sur _L3913_."

